column5: Mom and I were looking through the old photos last night and she was telling me my grandparents took her and her brother and sister (Uncle Bob and Auntie Pat) to Lake Simcoe all the time, renting cabins most weekends at Willow Beach and staying at Mossington Park.  There were tons of photos and this one I took a pic of to see if it has changed much since 1940.  Its an aerial shot of the area from back then.  Anyone live in the area and has it changed much?    Joey
Use Google satellite maps. Zoom in on Sutton and look to the east of the river mouth.
I bet one thing that has changed considerably if the fishing! Must have been incredible back then, it's still pretty good now!
In the middle of the field,it looks like a make shift ball diamond ????????
Looks like just homes are there now.  Thanks for doing the photo touch ups Terry  Joey
